{"key":"processedPost-14491821","value":{"id":14491821,"first":14490962,"last":14495097,"when":1306039099,"utime":"05/22/11 07:38 AM","cleanedPost":"Disregard that.&nbsp; I found out from the gypsum manufacturer last time I got a truckload that the pelleted gypsum is actually powdered gypsum with a binding agent added to make it easier to spread with machinery.&nbsp; Powdered gypsum would clog up a spreader, but pelleted gypsum rolls right through.<br />The binding agent is water soluble, so all you need to do is mix it dry with your dry substrate material and when you add water, it will dissolve.&nbsp; There is no need to grind it.<br />RR"}}